#In section 1: For each scan chain, ordered list of scan cells are reported with the following information.
#     1. cell_order        :      cell index number where '0' is the scan cell closest to the scan-out(SO) pin
#     2. scanchain_ID      :      scan chain id in which the scan cell resides
#     3. cell_type         :      type of cell(latch/port/flop/scan-chain-segment/memory_instance)
#     4. shift_clock       :      clock for each scan cell(shift_clock)
#     5. clock_polarity    :      polarity of the global clock(shift_clock),rising edge(+) and falling edge(-)
#     6. hier_name         :      hierarchical name of the cell
#     7. lib_cell_name     :      Library name of the cell 
#     8. scanout           :      scan output port of the scan cell(Q/QB/dedicated_so_pin)
#
#     Related to Scan Coverage:
#     register             :      refers to both flip-flops and latches
#     test cells           :      refers to register for which 'test_cell' block is defined in .lib
#     tpregs               :      refers to retiming flops, lockup, transparent and shadow latches
#     scn_on_sc            :      scannable regs (excluding tpregs) on scan chain
#     scn_off_sc           :      scannable regs (excluding tpregs) outside scan chain
#     scn_off_sc_tc        :      scannable test cells (excluding tpregs) outside scan chain
#     uscn                 :      unscannable regs
#     uscn_tc              :      unscannable test cells
#     nscn_i               :      inferred no-scan regs
#     nscn_i_tc            :      inferred no-scan test cells (= nscn_i_tc_on_sc + nscn_i_tc_off_sc)
#     nscn_i_tc_on_sc      :      inferred no-scan test cells on scan chain
#     nscn_i_tc_off_sc     :      inferred no-scan test cells outside scan chain
#     
#     Scan Coverage        :      scan_chain= no, DS= pre_scan_stitched:=      scn_off_sc / (scn_off_sc + uscn + nscn_i)
#                          :      scan_chain= no, DS=post_scan_stitched:=   scn_off_sc_tc / (scn_off_sc_tc + uscn_tc + nscn_i_tc)
#                          :      scan_chain=yes, DS= pre_scan_stitched:=       scn_on_sc / (scn_on_sc + scn_off_sc + uscn + nscn_i)
#                          :      scan_chain=yes, DS=post_scan_stitched:=       scn_on_sc / (scn_on_sc + scn_off_sc_tc + uscn_tc + nscn_i_tc)
#     
#     Note                 :      Force no_scan and force_no_scan_coverage registers are not included in scan coverage calculation


#In section 2: Flip-flops which are not part of any valid scan chain are reported with the following information.
